  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An Emergency Initiative to Boost Rice Production in Ghana, Mali, Senegal, and Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Poor rice farmer families</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This Initiative aims to improve farmers&#x2019; access to rice seed and fertilizer and to expand knowledge on best-bet rice technologies. It aims to provide certified rice seed and mineral fertilizer inputs (procurement and distribution costs not covered by the project) to 40,000 farmers through existing distribution channels, such as the private sector, government and non-government agencies (i.e. Catholic Relief Services, CRS).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to boost total domestic rice production in these four countries by a total of 30 thousand tons of paddy rice, with a current market value of about US $21 million.</narrative>
  </description>
